<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-18T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-18T12:00:00-05:00" n="621" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d621">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 656.119/885</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LIB1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Laughlin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-18T17:00:00+00:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">November 18, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 5.46 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>3814. War Trade Board [from <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName>]:</p>
                            <p>No. 1895. Referring to telegram No. 595 from <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MG1">McFadden</persName> to you
                                November 16.<note n="1" xml:id="d621fn1">Not printed.</note> The
                                British have had in mind that the present Dutch agreement is made
                                with the Royal Netherlands Government and I think they are disposed
                                to tell the present Government that if a new Government should be
                                formed in Holland which was not approved by the Associated
                                Governments we would not be bound to grant the facilities according
                                to the proposed draft agreement. I should like to inquire whether
                                you are willing to adopt this policy and whether you are willing
                                that a separate letter should be written to the Dutch delegates
                                saying that the agreement is signed subject to these conditions.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LIB1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Laughlin</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>